;i:45;s:5:\"coast\";i:46;s:8:\"atlantic\";i:47;s:8:\"mountain\";}}i:18;a:25:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Glenoe\";s:3:\"url\";s:51:\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/thefella/29406972965/\";s:11:\"description\";s:1730:\"			<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/people/thefella/\">TheFella</a> posted a photo:</p>\n	\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/thefella/29406972965/\" title=\"Glenoe\"><img src=\"https://live.staticflickr.com/8540/29406972965_31ba8c133b_m.jpg\" width=\"166\" height=\"240\" alt=\"Glenoe\" /></a></p>\n\n<p><b><a href=\"https://thefella.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">TheFella</a> | <a href=\"https://f8workshops.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">f/8 Workshops</a> | <a href=\"http://www.instagram.com/thefella\" rel=\"nofollow\">Instagram</a> | <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/thefella\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a> | <a href=\"https://thefella.com/snapchat\" rel=\"nofollow\">Snapchat</a></b><br />\n<br />\n<b>-------</b><br />\n<br />\n<b><a href=\"https://thefella.com/photo/glenoe\" rel=\"nofollow\">thefella.com/photo/glenoe</a></b> <br />\n<br />\nA few weeks ago, I went back to Belfast, Northern Ireland, to see my friends and family (and for a shoot for Guardian Travel). One day, I decided to research some locations and I found out about this waterfall about 30 mins drive from my house. No-one I talked to had really heard of it! Well, here is Glenoe Waterfall, between Larne and Carrickfergus.<br />\n<br />\nIt was sunny, but raining and I couldn\'t get the composition I wanted from the edge, so I rolled up my jeans, took off my shoes and socks and waded through the river for about an hour. It was pretty cold and painful, and I kept getting splashes of water on the lens from being so low to the river, but I think it was worth it.<br />\n<br />\n<b>-------</b><br />\n<br />\n<b>No images in comments please.</b><br />\n<br />\n<b>Details</b><br />\n<i>Nikon D810 / ISO 160 / f/22 / 1/6s / Nikkor 14-24mm f/2.8G ED @ 24mm / Location: Country Antrim, United Kingdom</i></p>\";s:15:\"description_raw\";s:1338:\"<b><a href=\"https://thefella.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">TheFella</a> | <a href=\"https://f8workshops.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">f/8 Workshops</a> | <a href=\"http://www.instagram.com/thefella\" rel=\"nofollow\">Instagram</a> | <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/thefella\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a> | <a href=\"https://thefella.com/snapchat\" rel=\"nofollow\">Snapchat</a></b>\n\n<b>-------</b>\n\n<b><a href=\"https://thefella.com/photo/glenoe\" rel=\"nofollow\">thefella.com/photo/glenoe</a></b> \n\nA few weeks ago, I went back to Belfast, Northern Ireland, to see my friends and family (and for a shoot for Guardian Travel). One day, I decided to research some locations and I found out about this waterfall about 30 mins drive from my house. No-one I talked to had really heard of it! Well, here is Glenoe Waterfall, between Larne and Carrickfergus.\n\nIt was sunny, but raining and I couldn\'t get the composition I wanted from the edge, so I rolled up my jeans, took off my shoes and socks and waded through the river for about an hour. It was pretty cold and painful, and I kept getting splashes of water on the lens from being so low to the river, but I think it was worth it.\n\n<b>-------</b>\n\n<b>No images in comments please.</b>\n\n<b>Details</b>\n<i>Nikon D810 / ISO 160 / f/22 / 1/6s / Nikkor 14-24mm f/2.8G ED @ 24mm / Location: Country Antrim, United Kingdom</i>\n\";s:5:\"m_url\";s:63:\"https://live.staticflickr.com/8540/29406972965_31ba8c133b_m.jpg\";s:5:\"t_url\";s:63:\"https://live.staticflickr.com/8540/29406972965_31ba8c133b_s.jpg\";s:5:\"l_url\";s:61:\"https://live.staticflickr.com/8540/29406972965_31ba8c133b.jpg\";s:9:\"photo_xml\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"1472831035\";s:10:\"date_taken\";s:25:\"2016-08-09T12:43:26-08:00\";s:15:\"date_taken_nice\";s:16:\"August 9th, 2016\";s:4:\"guid\";s:18:\"/photo/29406972965\";s:11:\"author_name\";s:8:\"TheFella\";s:10:\"author_url\";s:39:\"https://www.flickr.com/people/thefella/\";s:11:\"auth